"```sql\nSELECT COUNT(DISTINCT Examination.ID)\nFROM Examination\nJOIN Patient ON Examination.ID = Patient.ID\nJOIN Laboratory ON Examination.ID = Laboratory.ID\nWHERE Laboratory.SC170 IN ('negative', '0')\n  AND Patient.SEX = 'F'\n  AND (Examination.Symptoms IS NULL OR Examination.Symptoms = '');\n```\n\nThis SQL query counts the number of distinct patients who have a normal anti-scl70 test result, are female, and do not have any recorded symptoms. It joins the `Examination`, `Patient`, and `Laboratory` tables based on the foreign key relationships and applies the conditions specified in the evidence."